byline.original: By EMMA G. FITZSIMMONS and JASON GRANT

headline.print_headline: Transit Pact  in New Jersey  Is Still Elusive
headline.main: N.J. Transit Labor Talks Resume, but No Deal Is Reached

snippet: The rail unions were angered by a warning from the agency that health benefits would be suspended in a strike, which could begin in two days.
abstract: Negotiators for New Jersey Transit and rail workers unions meet again, two days before rail workers plan on going on strike, but fail to come to agreement.
